  "sections": {
    "Description": "The Moth is a 3-health, 3-move flying Vek that fires an artillery attack much like theScarab, flying over any tiles to land on the target and deal 1 point of damage. This attack pushes the affected target and the Moth itself away by one tile.\nMoths cannot spawn on an island with any other flying Vek (Hornet,Mosquito) other than the island's Psion. In addition, they also cannot spawn with either Scarabs orCrabs.",
    "Strategy": "The Moth is the most dangerous regular flying Vek, as in tight spaces it is very likely to be knocked back into a building, dealing heavy damage to your grid. Avoid choosing an island with Moths as your first island; being common enemies with high health, most starting weapons are unable to defeat them consistently in the early game, and with flight they can't bedrownedor dropped intochasmseither. Pushing it into tiles where they can be recoiled into other Vek is a great way of using its attack to your advantage, especially withForce Amp.",
    "Trivia": "  - Moths were previously able to spawn alongside Scarabs and Crabs. This is no longer the case as of version 1.2.76b."
