  "full_text": "Moth\nDetails\nHealth\n3\nMove\n3\nSystems\nRepulsive Pellets\n(\nEnemy\n)\nEffect\nLaunch an artillery attack for 1 damage, pushing shooter and target.\nSpecial\nFlying\n: Flying units can move over any terrain tile.\nThe\nMoth\nis a flying\nVek\nfrom\nInto The Breach\nintroduced in the Advanced Edition. They are only present if Advanced Enemies are turned on at the start of a new timeline.\nDescription\n[\n]\nThe Moth is a 3-health, 3-move flying Vek that fires an artillery attack much like the\nScarab\n, flying over any tiles to land on the target and deal 1 point of damage. This attack pushes the affected target and the Moth itself away by one tile.\nMoths cannot spawn on an island with any other flying Vek (Hornet,\nMosquito\n) other than the island's Psion. In addition, they also cannot spawn with either Scarabs or\nCrabs\n.\nStrategy\n[\n]\nThe Moth is the most dangerous regular flying Vek, as in tight spaces it is very likely to be knocked back into a building, dealing heavy damage to your grid. Avoid choosing an island with Moths as your first island; being common enemies with high health, most starting weapons are unable to defeat them consistently in the early game, and with flight they can't be\ndrowned\nor dropped into\nchasms\neither. Pushing it into tiles where they can be recoiled into other Vek is a great way of using its attack to your advantage, especially with\nForce Amp\n.\nTrivia\n[\n]\nMoths were previously able to spawn alongside Scarabs and Crabs. This is no longer the case as of version 1.2.76b.\nv\n\u00b7\nd\n\u00b7\ne\nVek\nVek\nBeetle\n\u2022\nBlobber\n\u2022\nBurrower\n\u2022\nCentipede\n\u2022\nCrab\n\u2022\nDigger\n\u2022\nFirefly\n\u2022\nHornet\n\u2022\nLeaper\n\u2022\nScarab\n\u2022\nScorpion\n\u2022\nSpider\n\u2022\nVolatile Vek\nVek (Advanced Edition)\nBouncer\n\u2022\nGastropod\n\u2022\nMosquito\n\u2022\nMoth\n\u2022\nPlasmodia\n\u2022\nStarfish\n\u2022\nTumblebug\nAlpha Vek\nAlpha Beetle\n\u2022\nAlpha Blobber\n\u2022\nAlpha Burrower\n\u2022\nAlpha Centipede\n\u2022\nAlpha Crab\n\u2022\nAlpha Digger\n\u2022\nAlpha Firefly\n\u2022\nAlpha Hornet\n\u2022\nAlpha Leaper\n\u2022\nAlpha Scarab\n\u2022\nAlpha Scorpion\n\u2022\nAlpha Spider\nAlpha Vek (Advanced Edition)\nAlpha Bouncer\n\u2022\nAlpha Gastropod\n\u2022\nAlpha Mosquito\n\u2022\nAlpha Moth\n\u2022\nAlpha Plasmodia\n\u2022\nAlpha Starfish\n\u2022\nAlpha Tumblebug\nVek Psions\nBlast Psion\n\u2022\nBlood Psion\n\u2022\nShell Psion\n\u2022\nSoldier Psion\nVek Psions (Advanced Edition)\nArachnid Psion\n\u2022\nRaging Psion\n\u2022\nSmoldering Psion\nVek Minions\nBlob\n\u2022\nAlpha Blob\n\u2022\nSpiderling Egg\n\u2022\nSpiderling\n\u2022\nAlpha Spiderling\nVek Minions (Advanced Edition)\nSpore\n\u2022\nAlpha Spore\n\u2022\nVicious Spore\n\u2022\nBlob Leader\nVek Leaders\nBeetle Leader\n\u2022\nFirefly Leader\n\u2022\nHornet Leader\n\u2022\nLarge Goo\n(\nMedium Goo\n) (\nSmall Goo\n) \u2022\nPsion Abomination\n\u2022\nScorpion Leader\n\u2022\nSpider Leader\nVek Leaders (Advanced Edition)\nBlobber Leader\n\u2022\nBouncer Leader\n\u2022\nCentipede Leader\n\u2022\nCrab Leader\n\u2022\nGastropod Leader\n\u2022\nMosquito Leader\n\u2022\nPlasmodia Leader\n\u2022\nScarab Leader\n\u2022\nStarfish Leader\n\u2022\nTumblebug Leader",
